# Restore terminal state after Claude Code TUI exits uncleanly (e.g. killed by SIGTERM in ralph loop)
# Claude v2.1.84 seem to leave the terminal in corrupted state.
# Source: https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/issues/38761
# Usage:
# $ claude-terminal-fix
setopt local_options err_return
stty sane 2>/dev/null || true
printf '\e[?1049l'                   # exit alternate screen
printf '\e[?25h'                     # show cursor
printf '\e[0m'                       # reset SGR attributes
printf '\e[?1000l\e[?1003l\e[?1006l' # disable mouse tracking
printf '\e[<u'                       # kitty: restore keyboard protocol stack
printf '\e[=0u'                      # kitty: reset keyboard protocol
